|CK0  The Brotherhood keeps a Wooden Man Post northeast of the main
|CK0  training hall. It is built for repetition: striking, checking,
|CK0  trapping, stance changes, and full combo chains.

|CK0  From the main training room, go "northeast". Once there, use:

|CK0      kill post
|CK0      attack post
|CK0      stop practice
|CK0      mswitch <style>
|CK0      <monk skill> post

|CK0  The post is safe. It does not attack, deal damage, die, leave a
|CK0  corpse, grant experience, count as a kill, or advance quests. It
|CK0  exists only to let monks practice form and rhythm.

|CK0  When you are done, "stop practice" steps back from the post and
|CK0  ends the practice fight immediately.

|CK0  Practice is still real practice. Monk skills used on the post spend
|CK0  normal chi, spell points, and cooldowns, and your combo state and
|CK0  monk monitor update as they would in combat.

